      jacketquotes:
        "&ldquo;Tamora Pierce creates epic worlds populated by girls and women of  bravery, heart, and strength. Her work inspired a generation of writers  and continues to inspire us.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>HOLLY BLACK</b>, #1 <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br>&ldquo;Few  authors can slay so effectively with a single sentence&mdash;I mean  fist-in-the-air, shouting-at-my-book slay&mdash;as Tamora Pierce. All these  years later, I still draw strength from her words.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>MARIE LU</b>, #1 <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce is a seminal figure in the fantasy field of writing, turning out one terrific book after another.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>TERRY BROOKS</b>, New York Times bestselling author of the Sword of Shannara trilogy<br><br>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s  impossible to overstate Tamora Pierce&rsquo;s impact on children&rsquo;s  literature. Her tough, wise, and wonderful heroines have inspired  generations of readers.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>RAE CARSON</b>, <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br> &ldquo;In the world of YA fantasy, there&rsquo;s before Tamora Pierce, and then  after her female heroes started kicking down the doors (and walls, and  other barriers)!&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>BRUCE COVILLE</b>, <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce is a trailblazer for so many fantasy writers, hacking  through the old tropes with her narrative machete and showing us that  girl-centered adventures are not just possible but amazing.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>RACHEL HARTMAN</b>, <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce&rsquo;s writing is like water from the swiftest, most refreshingly clear, invigorating, and revitalizing river.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>GARTH NIX</b>, <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br>&ldquo;Tamora  Pierce is gloriously unafraid to give her readers joy and laughter  along with adventure and struggle, to let us love her characters  wholeheartedly and find the best of ourselves in them.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>NAOMI NOVIK</b>, <i>New York Times</i> bestselling author<br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce and her brilliant heroines didn&rsquo;t just break down barriers; they smashed them with magical fire.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>KATHERINE ARDEN</b>, author of <i>The Bear and the Nightingale</i><br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce&rsquo;s bold, courageous heroines illuminate the journey to womanhood.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>CALLIE BATES</b>, author of <i>The Waking Land</i><br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce is the queen of YA fantasy, and we are all happy subjects in her court.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>JESSICA CLUESS</b>, author of <i>A Shadow Bright and Burning</i><br><br> &ldquo;Tamora Pierce&rsquo;s novels gave me a different way of seeing the world.  They were like nothing I&rsquo;d encountered before. Alanna stormed her way  into my thirteen-year-old heart and told me that I could write gorgeous,  complicated novels about vibrantly real people in fantastic situations,  and to be honest, she&rsquo;s never left.&rdquo;<br> &mdash;<b>ALAYA DAWN JOHNSON</b>, award-winning author of <i>Love Is the Drug</i>",
